      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Gertrude Esther Chapin (1881-?) was an American high school teacher, author and poet.  Born in Macgregor, Iowa, she 
	  graduated from Carleton University (1904) and later received her M.A. from the University of Iowa (1917).  She also studied 
	  at the University of Minnesota (1907), University of Chicago (1909-1910), and Coe College (1933 and 1949-1950).  For nearly 
	  forty years, from 1919 to 1952, she taught high school English in Cedar Rapids, Iowa.  She was a member of various literary 
	  societies, and her work appeared in numerous national magazines.  She is the author of <emph render="italic">Prairie Songs</emph>
	  (1953).</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
